winning_structure.name: UBX-CFG-VALGET
winning_structure.description: Get configuration items response. This message is output by the receiver to return requested configuration data (key and value pairs).

variable.description: Total payload length is 4 bytes plus N bytes for the variable-length cfgData field.

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x01 for this version)

fields.name: layer
fields.description: The layer from which the configuration item was retrieved: 0 - RAM layer, 1 - BBR, 2 - Flash, 7 - Default

fields.name: position
fields.description: Number of configuration items skipped in the result set before constructing this message (mirrors the equivalent field in the request message)

fields.name: cfgData
fields.description: Configuration data (key and value pairs). This field contains a sequence of U4 Key IDs followed by values of varying sizes (U1, U2, U4, or U8) depending on the Key ID. Due to its variable internal structure, it is represented as a raw byte array filling the remaining payload.

variable.notes: N is the number of configuration key IDs

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x01 for this version)

fields.name: layers
fields.description: The layers where the configuration should be deleted from

bits.name: bbr
bits.description: Delete configuration from the BBR layer

bits.name: flash
bits.description: Delete configuration from the Flash layer

fields.name: transaction
fields.description: Transaction action to be applied:

bits.name: action
bits.description: Transaction action: 0 = Transactionless UBX-CFG-VALDEL, 1 = (Re)Start deletion transaction, 2 = Deletion transaction ongoing, 3 = Apply and end a deletion transaction.

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: keyID
fields.description: Configuration key ID of a configuration item to be deleted

structure.name: UBX-CFG-VALGET
structure.description: Poll request to get configuration values by providing a list of configuration key IDs.

variable.description: Payload length is 4 bytes (for version, layer, position) plus 4 bytes for each Configuration Key ID. The number of keys (num_keys) can range from 0 to 64.
